primary_outcome.description:
A patient will be considered to have recovered once he or she meets the following criteria:
is afebrile (<38.0° C core temperature) for at least 48 hours without use of antipyretics;
all symptoms have resolved or returned to pre- illness levels (e.g., if patient had respiratory compromise prior to the onset of COVID-19), except for:
fatigue, anosmia, ageusia or dysgeusia, which may be persistent at level similar to that during the acute illness, i.e., the same level per symptom questionnaire;
chest pain, cough or dyspnea which if persistent must be at least one grade lower than at the start of treatment and no worse than grade 1 (mild). A symptom questionnaire generally following the FDA guidance, Assessing COVID-19-Related Symptoms in Outpatient Adult and Adolescent Subject in Clinical Trials of Drugs and Biological Products for COVID-19 Prevention or Treatment, September, 2020, for both the terms and severity grading, will be used to capture symptomology.
